Dot Plot Charts

Horizontal and vertical dot plots use the size and coloring of bubbles to display multiple dimensions and measures. Use dot plots to visualize related data to compare performance or locate unusual values.

Create a Horizontal Dot Plot

In the lens, click  and then select the Horizontal Dot Plot chart type.
In the X-Axis field, add the measure that you want to analyze.
In the Y-Axis field, add at least one dimension.
In the Bubble Size field, add the measure that determines bubble size.
In the Bubbles field, add dimension that determines different types of bubbles.
